			  -*- mode: text -*-

MASP Assembly Preprocessor Installation Instructions
====================================================

Build requirements
------------------
- C compiler (GCC/Clang)
- CMake 3.15+ (recommended)
- Optional: external libiberty (from binutils). If not found, a bundled copy
  is built automatically.

Quick build (CMake)
-------------------
mkdir -p build-cmake
cmake -S . -B build-cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build-cmake -j

This will produce the 'masp' executable under:
  build-cmake/src/masp

Install
-------
By default, install path is /usr/local.

cmake --install build-cmake --prefix /usr/local

To install under /usr use:

cmake --install build-cmake --prefix /usr

External libiberty (optional)
-----------------------------
MASP prefers a system libiberty if available; otherwise it builds the bundled
copy. To require a system libiberty set:

cmake -S . -B build-cmake -DBUILD_INTERNAL_LIBIBERTY=OFF

Package names (examples):
- Debian/Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install binutils-dev
- Fedora/RHEL:   sudo dnf install binutils-devel
- macOS (Homebrew): brew install binutils

If CMake cannot find libiberty automatically, provide hints:

cmake -S . -B build-cmake \
  -DBUILD_INTERNAL_LIBIBERTY=OFF \
  -DLIBIBERTY_LIBRARY=/path/to/libiberty.a \
  -DLIBIBERTY_INCLUDE_DIR=/path/to/include

Uninstall
---------
CMake does not generate an uninstall target by default. To uninstall, remove
the installed 'masp' binary from the chosen prefix (e.g. /usr/local/bin/masp).

Notes
-----
- Legacy autotools files and workflow have been removed; use CMake.
- There is currently no additional documentation or configuration files.